Title : 2014 Mutua Madrid Open – Women's Singles
Text : {{TennisEvents|2014|Mutua Madrid Open|
|champ = {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Maria Sharapova]]
|runner= {{flagicon|ROU}} [[Simona Halep]]
|score = 1–6, 6–2, 6–3
|before_name=Mutua Madrid Open – Women's Singles
|after_name=Mutua Madrid Open – Women's Singles
}}

{{main|2014 Mutua Madrid Open}}
[[Serena Williams]] was the two-time defending champion, but withdrew before her quarterfinal match because of a left thigh injury.<ref>[http://www.sportinglife.com/tennis/news/article/553/9303321/tennis-serena-williams-ruled-out-of-madrid-and-rome-due-to-thigh-problem Injury woe for Serena], ''Sporting Life'', 9 May 2014</ref>

[[Maria Sharapova]], runner-up in [[2013 Mutua Madrid Open – Women's Singles|2013]], claimed the title by beating [[Simona Halep]] in three sets in the final, 1–6, 6–2, 6–3.

